  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a multicentre, extension study of LUM001 in children diagnosed with Alagille Syndrome
      who have completed participation in a core LUM001 treatment protocol. The primary objective
      is to evaluate long-term safety and tolerability of LUM001. Efficacy will be assessed by
      evaluating the effect of LUM001 on the biochemical markers and pruritus associated with
      Alagille Syndrome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
